---

import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro"
import TopLayout from "@layouts/TopLayout.astro"
import BottomLayout from "@layouts/BottomLayout.astro"
import { RESEARCH } from "@consts"
---

<PageLayout title={RESEARCH.TITLE} description={RESEARCH.DESCRIPTION}>
  <TopLayout>
    <div class="animate">
      <h1 class="text-highlight-light text-5xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold">
        Research
      </h1>

  <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mt-3 opacity-75">
    MASTER'S THESIS • NEUSTEM LAB • UNIVERSITY OF MIAMI
  </div>

  <p class="text-lg mt-6 max-w-3xl">
    My master's thesis research focused on
    <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
      Schwann cell-nanoparticle interactions
    </span>
    in neural lesion models, with an emphasis on biomaterial design,
    cellular uptake, and applications in
    <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
      spinal cord injury
    </span>
    research.
  </p>
</div>

  </TopLayout>

  <BottomLayout>
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none animate">
      <section>
        <div class="text-sm tracking-widest mt-3 opacity-75">
          Research poster as presented at the 2025 University of Miami Neuroscience Research Day
        </div>

    <a
      href="/research/poster.png"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >
      <img
        src="/research/poster.png"
        alt="Master's thesis research poster"
        class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 dark:border-white/25 shadow-sm"
      />
    </a>

    <p>
      <a
        href="/research/poster.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="font-semibold"
      >
        Download full poster as PDF
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2>Project Overview</h2>

    <p>
      This project investigates how engineered
      <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
        chondroitin sulfate nanoparticles
      </span>
      interact with cells and biological debris in lesion-like environments.
      The broader goal is to better understand how nanoparticle properties
      influence uptake, compatibility, and potential therapeutic delivery
      in nervous system injury models.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2>Key Research Questions</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>How do Schwann cells interact with engineered nanoparticles?</li>
      <li>How does nanoparticle dose affect cellular uptake and viability?</li>
      <li>Can nanoparticle systems be studied alongside myelin debris in neural lesion models?</li>
      <li>How can biomaterial properties be tuned for regenerative medicine applications?</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2>Methods and Techniques</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
          Schwann cell culture
        </span>
        and cell maintenance
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
          Nanoparticle synthesis
        </span>
        and characterization
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
          Confocal microscopy
        </span>
        for uptake analysis
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
          MTS, DMMB, and BCA assays
        </span>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
          CNS myelin debris isolation
        </span>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
          Fiji/ImageJ
        </span>
        image processing
      </li>

      <li>
        Assistance with
        <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
          rat surgeries
        </span>
        for wound-healing studies
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2>Research Significance</h2>

    <p>
      Spinal cord injury creates a complex lesion environment involving
      cellular stress, inflammatory signaling, myelin debris, and limited
      regenerative capacity. This research contributes to the development
      of biomaterial-based strategies that may support future approaches in
      <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
        neural repair
      </span>,
      <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
        drug delivery
      </span>,
      and
      <span class="font-semibold dark:font-bold dark:text-white">
        regenerative medicine
      </span>.
    </p>
  </section>
</article>

  </BottomLayout>
</PageLayout>
